Package org.kobe.xbot.ClientLite

Class XTablesClient

java.lang.Object
org.kobe.xbot.ClientLite.XTablesClient
public class XTablesClient extends Object
Handles client-side interactions with the XTablesServer server. This class provides various constructors to connect to the XTablesServer server using different configurations: direct connection with specified address and port, or service discovery via mDNS with optional settings.

The XTablesClient class supports operations like caching, subscribing to updates and delete events, running scripts and managing key-value pairs. It uses Gson for JSON parsing and integrates with a custom SocketClient for network communication.

Author:
Kobe

  • Constructor Details

    • XTablesClient

      public XTablesClient(int SERVER_PORT, int MAX_THREADS, boolean useCache)
      Connects to the XTablesServer instance using the system-level DNS resolver and port with direct connection settings.
      Parameters:
      SERVER_PORT - the port of the server to connect to.
      MAX_THREADS - the maximum number of threads to use for client operations.
      useCache - flag indicating whether to use caching.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the server port is 5353, which is reserved for mDNS services.
